National Security Advisor Tom Donilon spoke with Bahraini Crown Prince Salman bin Hamad al-Khalifa to discuss President Obama's condemnation of violence against peaceful protesters in Bahrain. Donilon expressed support for the Crown Prince's efforts to show restraint and initiate dialogue with all segments of Bahraini society. The United States believes that the stability of Bahrain depends on respecting the universal rights of its people and implementing meaningful reform that addresses the aspirations of all Bahrainis.